At the heart of disability management lies cooperation
====================================

<img src="kaavio.jpg" alt="kaavio" height="400">

Good disability management practices 
====================================

* Managers have adopted clear, adequately and comprehensively specified procedures
* Management procedures are well documented: no individual interdependencies
* Activity is strategic in nature:
    * Key figures
    * Objectives
    * Continuous monitoring and development

More good practice
====================================
* Cooperation in occupational health care is of a high standard: customer has the right to lay claims to the occupational health care provider 
* The scale and structure of disability costs are better understood
    * HR departments have appropriate resources and a mandate to act so problems are detected early and treated with adequate measures
    * Managers and directors in the industry recognise that taking care of work disability is part of productivity 
    * An easy ”target for cutbacks” for the management  
* Work engagement factor is mostly forgotten



